1Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Sequence
Q1. Create a sequence to generate employee IDs starting from 1001.
Answer
sql
Copy code
CREATE SEQUENCE emp_seq
START WITH 1001
INCREMENT BY 1
NOCACHE;
2Ô∏è‚É£ Using a Sequence in INSERT
Q2. Insert a new employee using emp_seq for emp_id.
Answer
sql
Copy code
INSERT INTO Employees(emp_id, name, salary)
VALUES (emp_seq.NEXTVAL, 'David', 55000);
3Ô∏è‚É£ Creating an Index
Q3. Create an index on the name column of Employees.
Answer
sql
Copy code
CREATE INDEX idx_emp_name ON Employees(name);
4Ô∏è‚É£ Dropping an Index
Q4. Drop the index idx_emp_name.
Answer
sql
Copy code
DROP INDEX idx_emp_name;
5Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Synonym
Q5. Create a synonym emp for the Employees table.
Answer
sql
Copy code
CREATE SYNONYM emp FOR Employees;
6Ô∏è‚É£ Dropping a Synonym
Q6. Drop the synonym emp.
sql
Copy code
DROP SYNONYM emp;
7Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Database View
Q7. Create a view HighSalaryEmployees for employees with salary > 50000.
sql
Copy code
CREATE VIEW HighSalaryEmployees AS
SELECT emp_id, name, salary
FROM Employees
WHERE salary > 50000;
8Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Materialized View
Q8. Create a materialized view to store total salary per department.
sql
Copy code
CREATE MATERIALIZED VIEW DeptSalarySummary AS
SELECT dept_id, SUM(salary) AS total_salary
FROM Employees
GROUP BY dept_id;
9Ô∏è‚É£ Creating a Table Partition
Q9. Partition Orders table by range of order_date.
sql
Copy code
CREATE TABLE Orders_Partitioned (
    order_id NUMBER,
    order_date DATE,
    customer_id NUMBER,
    amount NUMBER
)
PARTITION BY RANGE(order_date) (
    PARTITION p1 VALUES LESS THAN (TO_DATE('2024-01-01','YYYY-MM-DD')),
    PARTITION p2 VALUES LESS THAN (TO_DATE('2025-01-01','YYYY-MM-DD'))
);
üîü Creating a Database Link
Q10. Create a database link to another database.
sql
Copy code
CREATE DATABASE LINK remote_db
CONNECT TO remote_user IDENTIFIED BY password
USING 'remote_tns';
